open-philip-babymonitor

Builds on prior reverse-engineering work, all MIT-licensed:

- aventproxy (https://github.com/thekoma/aventproxy)
  Source of the Philips Avent / Tuya Mobile SDK reverse engineering: request
  signing, password + email-MFA login, MQTT credential derivation, and the
  WebRTC→RTSP bridge. The bridge in `bridge/` is vendored from this project
  (commit 9d1ae98) and is bundled inside the app. The Swift Tuya client in
  `app/Sources/BabyMonitorCore` reimplements its documented API.

- tuya-ipc-terminal (https://github.com/seydx/tuya-ipc-terminal)
  The bridge that aventproxy forked from.

- go2rtc (https://github.com/AlexxIT/go2rtc)
  WebRTC and codec utilities used by the bridge.

The app also bundles a static build of FFmpeg (https://ffmpeg.org), used to
repackage the camera's RTSP into HLS. FFmpeg is licensed under the LGPL/GPL; the
binary is bundled unmodified and invoked as a separate process. Provide the
corresponding source per its license when distributing.

Unofficial. Not affiliated with Philips or Tuya.
